From: tawc
Origin: own

Add a tawc-namespaced C entry point inside libgfxstream_backend.so
that maps a gfxstream ColorBuffer handle to the underlying
AHardwareBuffer*.

Used by the tawc compositor's tawc_gfxstream Wayland protocol
handler: when a chroot client posts a swapchain image via that
protocol, the compositor needs to recover the AHB so it can import
it as a GLES texture (same path the libhybris/android_wlegl backend
uses). The chroot allocates the ColorBuffer through the kumquat
RESOURCE_CREATE_BLOB path, and gfxstream's host-side FrameBuffer
binds it to a real AHB via the AndroidAHB external-memory branch in
allocExternalMemory(). Both halves run in-process inside the
compositor, so once we have the handle a single C call into the
shared library is enough -- no IPC, no fd round trip.

Living inside frame_buffer.cpp (rather than a separate C++ shim in
the compositor crate) means the call has direct access to gfxstream's
private types and avoids forcing the Rust crate's build to ingest
gfxstream's full include tree (host/, host/include/, host/common/include/,
common/base/include/). The ABI surface is one symbol returning void*.

The returned AHB has its refcount bumped (gfxstream's
vkGetMemoryAndroidHardwareBufferANDROID does that internally).
The caller must AHardwareBuffer_release it when done.

See notes/gfxstream-bridge.md "WSI plan: custom Vulkan WSI" for
the surrounding design.

--- a/host/frame_buffer.cpp
+++ b/host/frame_buffer.cpp
@@ -16,6 +16,10 @@
 
 #include "frame_buffer.h"
 
+#if defined(__ANDROID__)
+#include <android/hardware_buffer.h>
+#endif
+
 #include <stdio.h>
 #include <string.h>
 #include <time.h>
@@ -5666,3 +5670,30 @@
 
 }  // namespace host
 }  // namespace gfxstream
+
+#if defined(__ANDROID__)
+// tawc-fork: extern "C" entry point for the tawc compositor's
+// tawc_gfxstream WSI protocol handler. Returns the AHardwareBuffer*
+// backing a given color-buffer handle, with refcount bumped (caller
+// must AHardwareBuffer_release). Returns NULL if the handle is
+// unknown or the color buffer isn't AHB-backed.
+//
+// Implementation: FrameBuffer::exportColorBuffer -> ColorBuffer::exportBlob
+// -> VkEmulation::exportColorBufferMemory -> vkGetMemoryAndroidHardwareBufferANDROID.
+// The last call returns an AHB with refcount += 1, which we hand to
+// the caller untouched — there is no intermediate owner.
+extern "C" AHardwareBuffer* tawc_gfxstream_lookup_ahb(uint32_t handle) {
+    auto* fb = gfxstream::host::FrameBuffer::getFB();
+    if (!fb) {
+        return nullptr;
+    }
+    auto info = fb->exportColorBuffer(static_cast<gfxstream::host::HandleType>(handle));
+    if (!info) {
+        return nullptr;
+    }
+    // descriptorInfo.handle is int64_t on Android, holding an
+    // AHardwareBuffer* (see external_object_manager.h, ExternalHandleInfo).
+    return reinterpret_cast<AHardwareBuffer*>(
+        static_cast<intptr_t>(info->descriptorInfo.handle));
+}
+#endif  // __ANDROID__
